item.description: Eudora- Biography Tom Chambers was born in Ogden, UT on June 21, 1959. Four-time NBA All-Star power forward/center as a member of the Seattle SuperSonics and Phoenix Suns in the 1980s; scored over 20,000 points in the NBA and the Suns retired his #24 jersey. When Charles Barkley joined the Suns, he teamed up with Chambers to create a fierce front-court combo. He was selected 8th overall in the 1981 NBA draft by the San Diego Clippers after four solid seasons at the University of Utah.
